The paper deals with a novel modulation and multiplexing method for wireless ad-hoc networks, which involves compressive sampling techniques and sparse modeling. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of low complexity algorithms, which could indicate a focus on Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed method in highly time dispersive environments, which could suggest a focus on Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
